laboratory_examinations.findings: The hepatic parenchyma appears within normal limits. The contour of the liver is smooth. A hyper echoic area in the hepatic dome measures 2.6 x 4.1 x 1.9 cm, corresponding to a hemangioma. No other hemangiomas identified. The main portal vein is patent. No ascites. No intrahepatic biliary dilation. The CHD measures 8 mm. Intimal wall stone is lodged in the neck of the gallbladder. There is trace gallbladder wall thickening and pericholecystic fluid. Sonographic Murphy's sign was positive. The imaged portion of the pancreas appears within normal limits. The spleen has normal echogenicity, measuring 10.5 cm. No hydronephrosis in the right kidney. Visualized portions of the aorta and IVC are within normal limits.
